      <section eId="sec_CCRP-771">
        <num>CCRP 771</num>
        <heading>771. Â Admonition</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-771__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the remark or comment is made by the judge, the district attorney, or a court official, and the remark is not within the scope of Article 770; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-771__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the remark or comment is made by a witness or person other than the judge, district attorney, or a court official, regardless of whether the remark or comment is within the scope of Article 770.
In such cases, on motion of the defendant, the court may grant a mistrial if it is satisfied that an admonition is not sufficient to assure the defendant a fair trial.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112768</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
